rComments: Dr. Hughes is a very intelligent, articulate and wonderful instructor. The exams and coursework were challenging, but they were also very clear and fairly laid out/marked. I learned a lot and found that there was a really nice flow in her teachings. Dr. Hughes cares about students and their quality of education. Would take any of her courses again.

Some issues with the course this year but I think they will be corrected later. She's a difficult prof and currently lacks empathy for students. It feels like an intro course but it's marked like she hates you. It's difficult to improve in this course because the marking is very unclear. I recommend avoiding this prof if you're trying to do well.

Not great at all. Likes psychology but wasn't clear on marking criteria, test grading, or anything else related to actual grades. So how much we loved psychology made no difference. She tries to teach well but she crams way too much in, and its hard to concentrate when you know it won't matter for the test.

She cares about material but is so disorganized/indifferent in how she presents it. Jumps between topics. Lectures aren't related, and always at least 60 slides, each with important material, she just reads them. TA is TERRIBLE but Hughes did nothing to correct that. Tests are ridiculous, essays are barely graded. Made me want to switch majors.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Humble Professor. Passionate about her field and about teaching it and it shows in every lecture. A Lot of content in this course and Dr. Hughes manages to push through 70+ slides per class at a graceful pace. Always accessible through email if you have questions and is honest with her students about expectations in the course. More like her!

Challenging content, but Dr Hughes does a fantastic job. Her lectures are engaging and you can tell she cares about her students. Grading on the exam can be tough, so make sure you use the same phrases and keywords she mentions in the lecture.

Pretty good professor and class. The last lecture was especially insightful and allowed me to see how much she really cares about critical topics within psychology and how much she is out there to help her students. The TA was pretty bad so the professor did extra work to help the students receive feedback. Overall, good class and professor
